---
title: Herby Chicken over Lemony Spaghetti with Zucchini
description: Love chicken alfredo? Then you’ll adore this dreamy dish. It’s a sophisticated riff on the classic with tons more flavor infused into every bite. There’s Italian-spiced chicken, tender zucchini, and al dente spaghetti all coated in a creamy, cheesy, lemon-spiked sauce. It’s hearty yet light and guaranteed to put a smile on any pasta-lover’s face.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-over-lemon-parm-spaghetti-09ad4100.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/herby-chicken-over-lemony-spaghetti-5f31851e577a571f1d54807f-90313187.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 480 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/herby-chicken-over-lemony-spaghetti-5f31851e577a571f1d54807f
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim
and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into
½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to #pot. Cook until al dente,
~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set
spaghetti aside. Keep empty pot handy for step 5.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably
nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While zucchini cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz}(patted dry) dry with paper
towels and season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.
Once zucchini is done, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in same
pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked
through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}
to rest. Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in #pot used for spaghetti over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and half the lemon zest. Cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{20-30%seconds}. Stir in ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for
4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and juice from 2 lemon wedges (4
wedges for 4). Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add spaghetti, zucchini, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp}(2 TBSP for
4 servings) to sauce; toss to coat. Add half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup} and
season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until
> spaghetti is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide between #bowls{}. Top with chicken. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan
and lemon zest. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.